Not yet.

820
01:23:35,393 --> 01:23:37,304
Want to get out of here?

821
01:23:38,833 --> 01:23:40,391
I think I better.

822
01:23:47,793 --> 01:23:49,545
I'll take the keys.

823
01:23:51,113 --> 01:23:52,512
I'm driving.

824
01:23:55,393 --> 01:24:00,626
I've never cheated on Betty.
Not once we were married, I mean.

825
01:24:01,753 --> 01:24:05,302
-Did you want to?
-Only about a thousand times.

826
01:24:08,673 --> 01:24:10,186
What do I do now?

827
01:24:12,513 --> 01:24:15,186
What's good enough for Mom
is good enough for me?

828
01:24:20,353 --> 01:24:21,911
What gets me...

829
01:24:22,953 --> 01:24:25,387
...is I'm in my forties.

830
01:24:25,753 --> 01:24:29,428
I've been in this crummy marriage
for over 20 years...

831
01:24:29,673 --> 01:24:33,871
...because that's what I was taught.
You stick things out.

832
01:24:34,113 --> 01:24:37,105
I don't recall when he made love to me
so intensely...

833
01:24:37,353 --> 01:24:39,503
...that he sent me to Africa.

834
01:24:39,753 --> 01:24:42,267
Frankly, I don't think he ever did.

835
01:24:43,313 --> 01:24:47,989
Now I find out that in between
bake sales, my mother was Anais Nin.

836
01:24:48,233 --> 01:24:49,348
What about me?

837
01:24:49,953 --> 01:24:52,069
I feel really weird.

838
01:24:52,313 --> 01:24:55,703
Like she cheated on me, not Dad.
Isn't that sick?

839
01:24:56,033 --> 01:24:58,866
When you're the only son
you sort of feel...

840
01:24:59,113 --> 01:25:03,072
...like the prince of the kingdom.
In your mind, you think...

841
01:25:03,313 --> 01:25:06,828
...your mother shouldn't want sex,
because she has you.

842
01:25:08,353 --> 01:25:10,184
You're right, that is sick.

843
01:25:13,313 --> 01:25:16,066
If she was so unhappy,
why didn't she leave?

844
01:25:30,273 --> 01:25:31,342
Can I...

845
01:25:31,793 --> 01:25:33,021
...read it now?

846
01:25:38,513 --> 01:25:40,469
Did I miss anything important?

847
01:25:44,513 --> 01:25:47,107
She just took him to her room.

848
01:25:47,353 --> 01:25:48,832
Dad's room?

849
01:25:49,793 --> 01:25:53,263
All right, you can skip that part.
Let's just start...

850
01:25:53,513 --> 01:25:54,628
...here.

851
01:26:04,673 --> 01:26:07,107
"Robert lay asleep in the bed.

852
01:26:07,993 --> 01:26:10,063
I was up all night that night.

853
01:26:11,153 --> 01:26:13,064
What happens tomorrow?

854
01:26:13,953 --> 01:26:16,911
He will leave
and everything new and unknown...

855
01:26:17,153 --> 01:26:19,383
...that had become so familiar..."

856
01:26:19,713 --> 01:26:21,066
...would be gone.

857
01:26:38,393 --> 01:26:39,826
Did you sleep well?

858
01:26:40,073 --> 01:26:41,222
Thanks.

859
01:26:42,553 --> 01:26:43,747
Good.

860
01:26:46,553 --> 01:26:48,783
-More coffee?
-Sure.

861
01:27:04,273 --> 01:27:07,583
I hope you don't mind my asking,
but I feel I should.

862
01:27:08,473 --> 01:27:09,792
What?

863
01:27:13,873 --> 01:27:18,503
These women friends of yours
all over the world, how does it work?

864
01:27:19,753 --> 01:27:24,065
Do you see some of them again,
or do you forget others?

865
01:27:24,753 --> 01:27:27,870
Or do you write to some of them
now and then?

866
01:27:28,113 --> 01:27:31,310
-How do you manage it?
-What do you mean?

867
01:27:31,833 --> 01:27:36,668
I just need to know the procedure,
so I don't upset your routine.

868
01:27:37,193 --> 01:27:38,262
Want some jam?

869
01:27:40,153 --> 01:27:43,111
What are you talking about?
There's no routine.

870
01:27:43,633 --> 01:27:45,191
Is that what you think this is?

871
01:27:46,193 --> 01:27:47,911
Well, what is this?

872
01:27:51,393 --> 01:27:53,031
Is it up to me?

873
01:27:54,393 --> 01:27:57,703
You're married with no intent
to leave your husband.

874
01:27:58,033 --> 01:27:59,227
To do what?

875
01:27:59,473 --> 01:28:03,989
Go off with someone who needs everyone,
but no one in particular?

876
01:28:04,233 --> 01:28:06,872
What would be the point?
Pass the butter, please.

877
01:28:07,993 --> 01:28:09,904
I was honest with you.

878
01:28:12,073 --> 01:28:14,792
Yes. Absolutely!

879
01:28:15,673 --> 01:28:20,622
You have this habit of not needing,
and that's very hard to break.

880
01:28:24,073 --> 01:28:26,633
In that case, why sleep?
You don't need rest.

881
01:28:27,833 --> 01:28:29,710
Why eat?
You don't need food.

882
01:28:30,313 --> 01:28:31,587
What're you doing?

883
01:28:32,073 --> 01:28:34,667
I'm not cut out to be a world citizen...

884
01:28:34,913 --> 01:28:37,302
...who experiences
everything and nothing.

885
01:28:37,593 --> 01:28:39,504
How do you know
what I experience?

886
01:28:41,433 --> 01:28:42,786
I know you.

887
01:28:43,833 --> 01:28:47,348
What can this possibly mean
to someone who doesn't need meaning...

888
01:28:47,593 --> 01:28:51,506
...who just goes with the mystery,
pretending he's not scared to death?

889
01:28:51,753 --> 01:28:53,232
Let's stop this right now!

890
01:28:53,513 --> 01:28:56,710
After you leave,
I'll have to sit here all my life...

891
01:28:56,953 --> 01:29:00,502
...and wonder what happened to me,
if anything.

892
01:29:01,593 --> 01:29:05,871
I'll have to wonder if you're in some
housewife's kitchen in Romania...

893
01:29:06,113 --> 01:29:10,982
...telling her of your world of good
friends, including me in that group.

894
01:29:11,353 --> 01:29:12,832
What should I say?

895
01:29:13,273 --> 01:29:17,152
I don't want you to say anything.
I don't need you to say anything.

896
01:29:17,473 --> 01:29:19,509
I want you to stop this now.

897
01:29:20,153 --> 01:29:21,506
Fine.

898
01:29:22,633 --> 01:29:25,705
More eggs? Or shall we fuck
on the linoleum one last time?

899
01:29:26,153 --> 01:29:29,862
-I won't apologize for who I am.
-No one asked you to.

900
01:29:30,113 --> 01:29:34,425
-I won't feel like I did anything wrong.
-You won't feel, period!

901
01:29:34,673 --> 01:29:37,824
You've carved yourself a part
in the world as a voyeur...

902
01:29:38,073 --> 01:29:40,541
...a hermit, a lover
when you feel like it.

903
01:29:40,793 --> 01:29:45,867
The rest of us are supposed to feel
grateful for this...Go to hell!

904
01:29:46,273 --> 01:29:50,061
It isn't human not to be lonely
and afraid!

905
01:29:50,313 --> 01:29:52,543
You're a hypocrite and a phony!

906
01:29:53,553 --> 01:29:55,464
I don't want to need you.

907
01:29:56,273 --> 01:29:57,547
Why?

908
01:29:58,073 --> 01:30:00,382
Because I can't have you.

909
01:30:02,313 --> 01:30:04,622
What difference does that make?

910
01:30:21,713 --> 01:30:23,146
Don't you see?

911
01:30:25,273 --> 01:30:29,505
Robert, don't you see?
I just have to know the truth.

912
01:30:29,993 --> 01:30:33,508
I have to know the truth,
because if I don't, I'll go crazy.

913
01:30:35,233 --> 01:30:36,951
So just tell me, either way.

914
01:30:37,193 --> 01:30:40,629
I can't act like this is enough
because it has to be.

915
01:30:41,233 --> 01:30:44,509
And I can't pretend not
to feel what I feel...

916
01:30:44,753 --> 01:30:46,471
...because it's over tomorrow.

917
01:30:50,353 --> 01:30:52,423
If I've done anything...

918
01:30:53,353 --> 01:30:54,672
...to make you think that...

919
01:30:54,913 --> 01:30:58,189
...what we have between us
is nothing new for me...

920
01:30:59,113 --> 01:31:01,149
...is just some routine...

921
01:31:02,473 --> 01:31:04,703
...then I do apologize.

922
01:31:09,593 --> 01:31:11,948
What makes it different?

923
01:31:15,513 --> 01:31:17,026
When I think...

924
01:31:17,273 --> 01:31:19,423
...of why I make pictures...

925
01:31:20,153 --> 01:31:22,906
...the only reason
I can come up with...

926
01:31:23,473 --> 01:31:27,261
It just seems
that I've been making my way here.

927
01:31:30,873 --> 01:31:33,865
Seems right now,
that all I've done in my life...

928
01:31:34,113 --> 01:31:36,229
...was making my way here to you.

929
01:31:38,713 --> 01:31:41,352
And if I think about
leaving here tomorrow...

930
01:31:41,593 --> 01:31:42,946
...without you...

931
01:32:00,233 --> 01:32:01,586
Don't let go.

932
01:32:05,273 --> 01:32:07,867
My God, what are we going to do?

933
01:32:30,233 --> 01:32:31,586
Where's your truck?

934
01:32:31,833 --> 01:32:34,472
It's out behind the barn.
I'll go...

935
01:32:34,993 --> 01:32:36,392
...upstairs.

936
01:32:52,033 --> 01:32:55,264
-Hi, Madge.
-I made some brown betty.

937
01:32:55,553 --> 01:32:57,828
Sent Floyd and the boy to town.
I said...

938
01:32:58,073 --> 01:33:01,429
..."I'm visiting my girlfriends
for the afternoon."

939
01:33:01,673 --> 01:33:04,187
He said, "Who will make lunch?"
I said...

940
01:33:04,433 --> 01:33:07,311
..."I'm taking a sick day.
Eat at the diner."

941
01:33:07,833 --> 01:33:11,064
Isn't that hilarious?
He didn't dare raise an eyebrow.

942
01:33:11,313 --> 01:33:14,908
I don't even want to tell you
how late he was out.

943
01:33:15,153 --> 01:33:19,465
Sorry 2 days passed before I came by.
With the boy home, time escapes me.

944
01:33:19,713 --> 01:33:22,591
Have you heard from Richard?
God, it's hot.

945
01:33:22,833 --> 01:33:25,188
Yes. It's hot.

946
01:33:59,673 --> 01:34:00,992
Come with me.

947
01:34:08,553 --> 01:34:10,225
Come away with me.

948
01:35:51,833 --> 01:35:53,186
Care for a beer?

949
01:35:53,593 --> 01:35:54,628
No.

950
01:36:11,593 --> 01:36:13,902
You're not coming with me, are you?

951
01:36:23,673 --> 01:36:27,348
No matter how many times
I turn it over in my mind...

952
01:36:29,153 --> 01:36:31,348
...it doesn't seem like the right thing.

953
01:36:33,033 --> 01:36:34,432
For who?

954
01:36:36,873 --> 01:36:38,306
For anyone.

955
01:36:41,033 --> 01:36:43,672
They'll never be able
to live through the talk.

956
01:36:46,913 --> 01:36:48,346
And Richard...

957
01:36:51,753 --> 01:36:55,109
