1029
01:41:57,513 --> 01:41:59,947
If that happens
you have to decide...

1030
01:42:00,193 --> 01:42:01,990
...because I can't.

1031
01:42:39,833 --> 01:42:41,664
I'll only say this once.

1032
01:42:44,033 --> 01:42:45,989
I've never said it before.

1033
01:42:46,953 --> 01:42:50,548
But this kind of certainty
comes just once in a lifetime.

1034
01:44:48,673 --> 01:44:49,901
Look!

1035
01:45:03,873 --> 01:45:06,467
-You got it.
-I couldn't sell him.

1036
01:45:06,713 --> 01:45:09,227
I know.
I knew you would win.

1037
01:45:09,473 --> 01:45:12,431
-Good girl. Proud of you.
-Thanks.

1038
01:45:12,673 --> 01:45:14,072
-Hi, Mom.
-Hi, darling.

1039
01:45:14,313 --> 01:45:16,383
-Did you eat?
-Yeah. I ate.

1040
01:45:17,633 --> 01:45:19,430
Hey, there.
How you doing?

1041
01:45:19,673 --> 01:45:22,392
It didn't take you too long to get here.

1042
01:45:25,873 --> 01:45:28,023
-We had fun.
-Are you hungry?

1043
01:45:28,273 --> 01:45:30,104
I got something for you.

1044
01:45:32,553 --> 01:45:34,066
The fair was great.

1045
01:45:39,633 --> 01:45:41,544
You all came home.

1046
01:45:41,793 --> 01:45:43,021
And, with you...

1047
01:45:43,273 --> 01:45:45,628
...my life of details.

1048
01:45:50,633 --> 01:45:53,830
A day or 2 passed,
and with each thought of him...

1049
01:45:54,073 --> 01:45:56,871
...a task would present itself
like a lifesaver...

1050
01:45:57,113 --> 01:46:00,503
...pulling me further away
from those 4 days.

1051
01:46:01,713 --> 01:46:03,351
I was grateful.

1052
01:46:03,633 --> 01:46:05,510
I felt safe.

1053
01:46:12,553 --> 01:46:16,432
Put me out of my misery.
I can’t stand the suspense.

1054
01:46:16,673 --> 01:46:18,504
I'm not talking about you.

1055
01:46:18,753 --> 01:46:21,790
I know I'm a goner.
I can’t stand the suspense. Shoot.

1056
01:46:22,033 --> 01:46:23,944
I don’t even need a blindfold.

1057
01:46:24,193 --> 01:46:27,708
Condemned man’s dinner.
Chicken, peas, watermelon.

1058
01:46:45,113 --> 01:46:49,789
-Do you want anything special?
-How about that brown sugar meat loaf?

1059
01:48:46,153 --> 01:48:48,951
For a moment,
I didn't know where I was.

1060
01:48:49,673 --> 01:48:53,666
And for a split second, I thought
that he didn't really want me.

1061
01:48:54,793 --> 01:48:57,068
That it was easy to walk away.

1062
01:49:36,153 --> 01:49:39,543
Robert leaned over as if to get
something from the glove box.

1063
01:49:40,793 --> 01:49:43,261
8 days ago, he'd done that...

1064
01:49:43,553 --> 01:49:46,147
...and his arm had
brushed across my leg.

1065
01:49:47,033 --> 01:49:50,150
A week ago I'd been in Des Moines,
buying a new dress.

1066
01:50:17,553 --> 01:50:19,589
That truck's a long way from home.

1067
01:50:20,073 --> 01:50:21,825
Washington State.

1068
01:50:22,313 --> 01:50:26,386
I'll bet it's that photographer
they talked about at the café.

1069
01:50:32,313 --> 01:50:34,508
What's he waiting for?

1070
01:51:06,073 --> 01:51:07,267
Come on!

1071
01:51:32,313 --> 01:51:33,507
Oh, no!

1072
01:51:37,913 --> 01:51:40,029
The words were inside of me.

1073
01:51:40,273 --> 01:51:43,504
"I was wrong, Robert, to stay,
but I can’t go.

1074
01:51:43,753 --> 01:51:46,472
Let me tell you again
why I can’t go.

1075
01:51:50,033 --> 01:51:52,786
Tell me again why I should go. "

1076
01:51:53,033 --> 01:51:56,025
I heard his voice coming back to me:

1077
01:51:56,513 --> 01:52:00,631
"This kind of certainty comes
once in a lifetime. "

1078
01:52:05,353 --> 01:52:06,706
What's wrong, Franny?

1079
01:52:10,793 --> 01:52:13,227
Will you please tell me what's wrong?

1080
01:52:16,553 --> 01:52:18,430
I just need a minute.

1081
01:53:20,793 --> 01:53:23,512
Dad, you bought the wrong feed!

1082
01:53:47,673 --> 01:53:50,824
I was grateful for the
silence that night.

1083
01:53:52,033 --> 01:53:55,548
I realized
love won’t obey our expectations.

1084
01:53:55,913 --> 01:53:59,223
Its mystery is pure and absolute.

1085
01:53:59,873 --> 01:54:01,545
What Robert and I had...

1086
01:54:01,793 --> 01:54:04,387
...could not continue
if we were together.

1087
01:54:04,873 --> 01:54:09,503
And what Richard and I shared
would vanish if we were apart.

1088
01:54:10,073 --> 01:54:12,871
But how I wanted to share this!

1089
01:54:13,673 --> 01:54:17,666
How would our lives have changed
if I had?

1090
01:54:18,153 --> 01:54:21,543
Could anyone else have seen
the beauty of it?

1091
01:54:26,473 --> 01:54:28,145
I'm Francesca Johnson.

1092
01:54:28,553 --> 01:54:30,145
And I...

1093
01:54:31,833 --> 01:54:35,667
I feel awful that I haven't visited
sooner. Is it a bad time?

1094
01:54:35,953 --> 01:54:38,513
Am I interrupting anything?
Is it too late?

1095
01:54:38,753 --> 01:54:40,709
No, not at all.

1096
01:54:41,233 --> 01:54:44,350
We became inseparable,
Lucy and I.

1097
01:54:45,473 --> 01:54:50,308
The funny thing is, I didn't tell her
about Robert until years later.

1098
01:54:53,593 --> 01:54:55,982
But for some reason,
being with her...

1099
01:54:56,233 --> 01:54:58,064
...somehow made me feel...

1100
01:54:58,713 --> 01:55:00,624
...it was safe to think about him...

1101
01:55:01,313 --> 01:55:03,031
...to continue loving him.

1102
01:55:05,193 --> 01:55:09,505
This town loved talking
about the two of us, but we didn't care.

1103
01:55:10,553 --> 01:55:12,384
And neither did your father.

1104
01:55:13,993 --> 01:55:15,392
It's time.

1105
01:55:34,313 --> 01:55:35,632
Is better?

1106
01:55:39,193 --> 01:55:40,592
Is better.

1107
01:56:09,713 --> 01:56:10,907
Franny.

1108
01:56:13,553 --> 01:56:15,783
I just want to say...

1109
01:56:18,193 --> 01:56:21,424
...I know you had your own dreams.

1110
01:56:24,233 --> 01:56:27,305
I'm sorry I couldn't give them to you.

1111
01:56:31,833 --> 01:56:34,552
I love you so very much.

1112
01:57:01,993 --> 01:57:05,144
After your father died,
I tried to get in touch with Robert...

1113
01:57:05,393 --> 01:57:08,271
...but he had left National Geographic.

1114
01:57:08,633 --> 01:57:10,908
No one seemed to know where he was.

1115
01:57:11,233 --> 01:57:15,431
My only connections to him
were the places we'd been that day.

1116
01:57:15,673 --> 01:57:18,790
And so, each year on my birthday...

1117
01:57:19,033 --> 01:57:20,466
...I'd revisit them.

1118
01:57:28,073 --> 01:57:31,463
Then one day,
I received a letter from his attorney...

1119
01:57:31,713 --> 01:57:33,032
...with a package.

1120
02:01:07,273 --> 02:01:11,346
There has not been a day since
that I have not thought of him.

1121
02:01:12,513 --> 02:01:15,983
When he said that we were no longer
2 people, he was right.

1122
02:01:20,113 --> 02:01:22,866
Bound together as tightly as
2 people can be.

1123
02:01:24,793 --> 02:01:26,863
If it hadn’t been for him...

1124
02:01:27,113 --> 02:01:30,742
...I could not have lasted on the farm
all those years.

1125
02:01:34,033 --> 02:01:36,672
Remember my dress you wanted, Carolyn?

1126
02:01:37,273 --> 02:01:39,912
The one you said I never wore?

1127
02:01:41,113 --> 02:01:42,785
I know I was silly...

1128
02:01:43,033 --> 02:01:47,629
...but it was like you wanted
to wear my wedding dress to the movies.

1129
02:01:51,433 --> 02:01:53,230
After reading all this...

1130
02:01:53,473 --> 02:01:57,386
...I hope you can now
understand my burial request.

1131
02:01:57,633 --> 02:02:00,625
It was not the ravings
of some mad old lady.

1132
02:02:00,913 --> 02:02:04,144
I gave my life to my family.

1133
02:02:04,393 --> 02:02:07,544
I wish to give Robert
what is left of me.

1134
02:02:07,993 --> 02:02:09,221
Hey, Dad.

1135
02:02:11,473 --> 02:02:13,270
Can I talk to you?

1136
02:02:19,073 --> 02:02:22,588
You've been gone all night.
Do I have the right to ask where?

1137
02:02:22,833 --> 02:02:25,108
Do I make you happy, Betty?

1138
02:02:25,353 --> 02:02:26,945
Because I want to.

1139
02:02:27,193 --> 02:02:28,865
More than anything.

1140
02:02:40,073 --> 02:02:41,665
Hi, Steve. It's me.

1141
02:02:41,913 --> 02:02:43,187
Good.

1142
02:02:43,433 --> 02:02:44,309
You?

1143
02:02:45,593 --> 02:02:47,823
Listen, we have to talk.

1144
02:02:48,393 --> 02:02:50,065
How about now?

1145
02:02:54,073 --> 02:02:56,667
I've decided to stay here for a while.

1146
02:02:58,073 --> 02:02:59,904
I don't know how long.

1147
02:03:00,753 --> 02:03:03,392
No, I'm not angry, Steve.

1148
02:03:04,233 --> 02:03:06,064
I'm not.

1149
02:03:06,313 --> 02:03:08,383
I'm not angry at all.

1150
02:03:10,073 --> 02:03:12,382
I gave Lucy his photography book.

1151
02:03:12,793 --> 02:03:15,591
If you're interested, take a look.

1152
02:03:15,953 --> 02:03:19,309
If my words still leave
some things unclear...

1153
02:03:19,553 --> 02:03:22,386
...perhaps his pictures can illuminate.

1154
02:03:22,833 --> 02:03:26,508
After all,
that's what an artist does best.

1155
02:03:35,033 --> 02:03:36,910
I love you both...

1156
02:03:37,153 --> 02:03:39,064
...with all my heart.

1157
02:03:40,273 --> 02:03:43,743
Do what you have to
to be happy in this life.

1158
02:03:44,593 --> 02:03:47,266
There is so much beauty.

1159
02:03:48,513 --> 02:03:51,073
Go well, my children.


